310 g Chicken Breast, Diced
¾ cup Basmati Rice
¼ cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
227 g Broccoli
1 tbsp Chicken Stock Powder
1 unit(s) Green Onion
2 unit(s) Cream Cheese
2 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Stir rice and stock powder into the pot of boiling water.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, 12-14 min.
Remove from heat. Set aside, still covered.

Meanwhile, heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
If desired, cut broccoli into bite-sized pieces.
When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then broccoli and 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) water. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until broccoli is tender-crisp, 4-5 min.
Transfer broccoli to a plate.

Reheat the same large non-stick pan over medium-high.
When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter, then the chicken. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring often, until golden-brown and cooked through, 5-6 min.**

Add rice, cream cheese, broccoli and 1/4 cup (1/2 cup) water or milk to the pan with chicken. Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine, 1 min.

Divide chicken-and-broccoli rice between bowls.
Sprinkle with cheese, then snip green onions over top.